WEBVTT

00:01.691 --> 00:03.865
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:03.900 --> 00:11.873
♪♪

00:11.908 --> 00:19.881
♪♪

00:25.818 --> 00:28.476
I'm just saying -- why do people
say grapefruit and tuna fish

00:28.511 --> 00:30.271
but not egg chicken
or beef mammal?

00:30.306 --> 00:32.170
Darwin: [ Whines ]

00:32.204 --> 00:33.516
Come on, Mr. Dad!

00:33.550 --> 00:35.518
When we said,
"come pick us up after school,"

00:35.552 --> 00:38.245
we didn't mean
after graduation!

00:38.279 --> 00:40.074
Get on the horse![ Horse whinnies ]

00:40.109 --> 00:41.075
What!?
What!? What!?

00:41.110 --> 00:42.904
No time to explain!

00:42.939 --> 00:45.286
Hyah!

00:48.220 --> 00:50.636
Let me guess --
you saw it, had to have it,

00:50.671 --> 00:53.018
and tried to let the kids
take the fall for it.

00:53.053 --> 00:54.985
-[ Whines ]
-What is he called?

00:55.020 --> 00:56.056
Wunderklopp.

00:56.090 --> 00:59.369
[ Neighs ]

00:59.404 --> 01:00.853
[ Sighs ]
It's okay.

01:00.888 --> 01:03.201
I've lined up a buyer
to take him off our hands.

01:03.235 --> 01:04.616
Wait, how can you
already have a buyer

01:04.650 --> 01:06.411
for a horse
Dad just brought home?

01:06.445 --> 01:08.516
Oh, sweetie, do you really think
I didn't expect your father

01:08.551 --> 01:10.691
to buy a horse at some point
in our marriage?

01:10.725 --> 01:12.417
The problem is
the guy can't buy it

01:12.451 --> 01:13.866
before the first
of next month.

01:13.901 --> 01:16.110
So short of having Wunderklopp
for breakfast...

01:16.145 --> 01:17.939
[ Wunderklopp whinnies ]

01:17.974 --> 01:19.251
...I'm open
to suggestions

01:19.286 --> 01:21.219
on how we're gonna survive
until then.

01:21.253 --> 01:22.530
All: Hmm.

01:22.565 --> 01:24.118
I guess we're gonna
have to tap into

01:24.153 --> 01:25.947
the money you saved
for me to go to college.

01:25.982 --> 01:28.088
[ Laughter ]

01:28.122 --> 01:29.158
What?

01:29.192 --> 01:31.056
I don't know
what's the funniest,

01:31.091 --> 01:32.402
the fact you think
you got a trust fund

01:32.437 --> 01:33.990
5or the fact you think
you'll make it to college.

01:34.024 --> 01:36.199
Well, you guys come up
with a solution then.

01:36.234 --> 01:38.236
I said I would never
go back to that life,

01:38.270 --> 01:39.858
that it was all
behind me.

01:39.892 --> 01:43.689
Sadly, the time has come
for me to call Don Luciano.

01:43.724 --> 01:45.312
[ Line rings]

01:45.346 --> 01:48.108
[ Telephone rings ]

01:48.142 --> 01:50.731
Don Luciano pizza!Richard, no!

01:50.765 --> 01:52.526
One of their pizzas
might have enough calories

01:52.560 --> 01:54.148
to keep us alive
for two weeks,

01:54.183 --> 01:56.633
but they've already taken
too many years off your life.

01:56.668 --> 01:58.773
Ricardo?
Is that you?

01:58.808 --> 01:59.602
No.

01:59.636 --> 02:01.776
Come back to us,
Ricardo.

02:01.811 --> 02:03.537
We are your real family.

02:03.571 --> 02:04.607
No!

02:04.641 --> 02:07.230
I take 10% off,
just for you.

02:07.265 --> 02:09.405
I'm sorry,
Don Luciano.

02:09.439 --> 02:12.442
You know the sad thing
about betrayal?

02:12.477 --> 02:15.065
It never comes
from an enemy.

02:15.100 --> 02:21.106
[ Line clicks ][ Sobbing ]

02:21.141 --> 02:22.694
Oh! I know!

02:22.728 --> 02:25.559
We invite people who need hugs
and kisses to come to our house

02:25.593 --> 02:27.699
and we give it to them
for money!

02:27.733 --> 02:30.736
Oh I know!
We all forget I just said that.

02:30.771 --> 02:31.944
Guys, don't panic!

02:31.979 --> 02:33.670
I spent the last of
this month's food money

02:33.705 --> 02:35.603
on a metal detector
and some lottery tickets.

02:35.638 --> 02:37.985
Worst-case scenario,
we can eat those.

02:38.019 --> 02:39.228
I've got an idea.

02:39.262 --> 02:40.781
We rent the house
as a bed and breakfast!

02:40.815 --> 02:42.645
Anais, we can't afford
our own breakfast,

02:42.679 --> 02:44.405
let alone pay for
other people.

02:44.440 --> 02:48.029
Fine. Then we rent the house as
a bed and...continue-to-fast.

02:48.064 --> 02:50.687
Hmm.

02:50.722 --> 02:52.517
Hmm. Hmm.

02:52.551 --> 02:53.966
Hmm.

02:54.001 --> 03:00.283
♪♪

03:00.318 --> 03:01.733
[ Doorbell rings ]

03:01.767 --> 03:03.044
Hello. Hello.

03:03.079 --> 03:04.529
Oh, please come in.

03:04.563 --> 03:06.945
I'm Ethel
and this is Bernie.

03:06.979 --> 03:08.464
Ha!
-Ha!

03:08.498 --> 03:12.192
Sorry, Bernie and I are making
a travel-map of our holiday.

03:12.226 --> 03:14.228
It's been our lifelong dream,
see.

03:14.263 --> 03:16.472
I think you're the first
tourists in Elmore

03:16.506 --> 03:18.405
since those two guys
back in '83.

03:18.439 --> 03:20.441
The town was so happy,
they put up a statue of them

03:20.476 --> 03:22.236
in the park with their motto
underneath --

03:22.271 --> 03:24.134
"Tell us the quickest way
out of this dump."

03:24.169 --> 03:25.550
[ Laughter ]

03:25.584 --> 03:26.827
Still,
beats our town.

03:26.861 --> 03:28.518
It's so small
we don't need phones.

03:28.553 --> 03:30.140
We just speak louder.

03:30.175 --> 03:31.556
[ Laughter ]

03:31.590 --> 03:34.317
I must say,
the house looks a bit different

03:34.352 --> 03:35.732
than the photo
on the ad.

03:35.767 --> 03:38.010
Oh, uh, they're just close-ups,
that's all.

03:38.045 --> 03:40.254
That one was taken right here
in the living room.

03:40.289 --> 03:42.256
Look.
-Right.

03:42.291 --> 03:43.740
Yeah, it also said
you had cable?

03:43.775 --> 03:45.777
Does it have subtitles
'cause our hearing is --

03:45.811 --> 03:48.020
Yes, let me talk you through
how it works.

03:48.055 --> 03:51.472
In here, you receive cable TV
from right across the street...

03:51.507 --> 03:53.888
until around 7:00 pm,
when they shut the blinds.

03:53.923 --> 03:56.028
[ Chuckles ]

03:56.063 --> 03:57.306
And how do we work the A/C?

03:57.340 --> 03:59.273
We get terrible migraines
in the heat, so...

03:59.308 --> 04:01.965
Oh. You can operate it
like so.

04:02.000 --> 04:03.898
Ah, refreshing.

04:03.933 --> 04:07.281
Sure. And, now, we also get
awful rheumatic fever

04:07.316 --> 04:09.525
and I think you had a hot tub
somewhere?

04:09.559 --> 04:11.734
Sure,
if you just follow me.

04:11.768 --> 04:13.977
I give you
the hot tub!

04:14.012 --> 04:15.358
[ Bubbling ]

04:15.393 --> 04:17.084
Okay, I guess it's time
for us to go.

04:17.118 --> 04:18.672
Wait.
Is the house sound-proofed?

04:18.706 --> 04:20.777
We suffer from
a rare ailment which --

04:20.812 --> 04:22.607
Payment?
Yes, we'll take cash. Bye!

04:22.641 --> 04:24.367
...rare ailment
which means...

04:24.402 --> 04:25.920
-Bye!
-...we freeze and faint...

04:25.955 --> 04:29.303
Kids: Bye!
...if anything loud
or surprising happens.

04:29.338 --> 04:31.063
[ Whinnies ]

04:32.858 --> 04:35.930
Enjoy your stay!

04:39.969 --> 04:42.696
♪♪

04:42.730 --> 04:43.904
Hm?

04:43.938 --> 04:45.526
♪♪

04:45.561 --> 04:47.770
I'm heading to the store.
Do we need anything?

04:47.804 --> 04:50.186
Uh, we need
the inside of an orange,

04:50.220 --> 04:51.463
the inside of
a stick of butter,

04:51.498 --> 04:52.982
the inside of
a carton of milk.

04:53.016 --> 04:56.365
And the inside of
a microwave oven.

04:56.399 --> 04:59.885
♪♪

04:59.920 --> 05:01.266
Ahh!

05:01.301 --> 05:02.681
[ Water running ]

05:06.547 --> 05:09.309
Why won't it wash off?

05:09.343 --> 05:11.103
[ Doorbell rings ]

05:11.138 --> 05:12.346
Ah.

05:12.381 --> 05:19.767
♪♪

05:19.802 --> 05:21.562
Huh?

05:24.393 --> 05:25.704
[ Grumbles ]

05:27.085 --> 05:29.121
Since when could you use
a computer like that?!

05:29.156 --> 05:30.468
I don't know, Bernie.

05:30.502 --> 05:32.470
It's like I have this
interior voice that woke up.

05:32.504 --> 05:33.954
Now I know that
I want my memes dank

05:33.988 --> 05:36.301
and none of that
cheezburger weak sauce.

05:36.336 --> 05:38.993
Okay.

05:40.098 --> 05:43.929
Gumball: Good. Now search
10 hours of saxophone Chihuahua.

05:43.964 --> 05:47.485
♪♪

05:47.519 --> 05:50.142
[ Toilet flushes ]

05:50.177 --> 05:51.972
[ Gulps ]

05:53.422 --> 05:56.977
Hm? Hmm.

05:57.011 --> 06:05.019
♪♪

06:05.054 --> 06:06.055
What is that?

06:06.089 --> 06:07.159
Ding.

06:07.194 --> 06:09.645
Oh,
must be the microwave.

06:09.679 --> 06:11.336
Ohh,
what is that?

06:11.371 --> 06:12.372
[ Clicks tongue ]

06:12.406 --> 06:14.512
Hmm.
Must be a melon.

06:14.546 --> 06:16.686
Now, what is that?

06:16.721 --> 06:19.724
I am a Black Forest gateau
with a crunchy shortbread base,

06:19.758 --> 06:23.003
multiple layers of praline,
and a glossy cocoa finish.

06:23.037 --> 06:24.349
[ All gasp ]

06:24.384 --> 06:25.764
Hmm. Must be
a Black Forest gateau

06:25.799 --> 06:27.352
with a crunchy shortbread base,

06:27.387 --> 06:30.424
multiple layers of praline,
and a glossy cocoa finish.

06:30.459 --> 06:31.805
[ All sigh ]

06:31.839 --> 06:32.599
Night, Ethel.

06:32.633 --> 06:33.910
Night, Bernie.

06:33.945 --> 06:35.843
♪♪

06:35.878 --> 06:38.225
I don't understand.
The bed looks big enough

06:38.259 --> 06:40.814
but it always feels like
I'm pressing against you.

06:40.848 --> 06:42.643
Yeah, and it looks like
there are more eyes

06:42.678 --> 06:44.542
than there should be
in here.

06:48.235 --> 06:49.547
[ Clicks tongue ]

06:50.133 --> 06:53.274
♪♪

06:53.309 --> 06:56.139
[ Both scream, bleat ]

06:56.174 --> 06:58.935
[ Groans ]

06:58.970 --> 06:59.833
-No!
-No!

06:59.867 --> 07:01.800
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.
No!

07:01.835 --> 07:03.353
[ Gasps ]
What have we done?

07:03.388 --> 07:04.976
Uh,
what's going on?

07:05.010 --> 07:06.253
[ Both gasp ]

07:06.287 --> 07:10.222
Uh, our guests had so much
fun that they...uh...

07:10.257 --> 07:11.500
They...

07:11.534 --> 07:13.640
They've gone into
hibernation.

07:13.674 --> 07:15.469
Wait --
do goats hibernate?

07:15.504 --> 07:16.746
Yep. Yeah, yeah.

07:16.781 --> 07:18.058
Aww.
Does that mean

07:18.092 --> 07:19.715
they won't be able to
finish their dream trip?

07:19.749 --> 07:22.856
Uh, I think it's safe
to say no, honey.

07:22.890 --> 07:24.478
Ah,
poor little goat dudes.

07:24.513 --> 07:26.342
I wish there was something
we could do to help.

07:26.376 --> 07:27.723
Oh, Gumball,
I'm sorry,

07:27.757 --> 07:29.725
but apart from literally
dragging them around town

07:29.759 --> 07:31.174
and taking pictures of them

07:31.209 --> 07:33.349
and then putting those photos
in their map thing

07:33.383 --> 07:34.661
so it looks like they had fun

07:34.695 --> 07:36.076
and then dumping them
on the train

07:36.110 --> 07:38.527
so they become
someone else's problem,

07:38.561 --> 07:40.390
I really don't know
how we can help.

07:40.425 --> 07:41.564
Let's just
do that then.

07:41.599 --> 07:43.428
[ Gasps ] No.

07:43.463 --> 07:44.429
Yes.

07:44.464 --> 07:52.713
♪♪

07:52.748 --> 07:56.786
♪ I've seen rainy days
and I've seen sunshine ♪

07:56.821 --> 07:58.685
♪ Been down in misery

07:58.719 --> 08:00.687
♪ But I bark out loud

08:00.721 --> 08:02.620
♪ Though I go to
every place I can ♪

08:02.654 --> 08:04.829
♪ Since all my travels
first began ♪

08:04.863 --> 08:06.762
♪ I still look forward to

08:06.796 --> 08:08.729
♪ Each day I spend with you

08:08.764 --> 08:10.386
♪ This much I know is true

08:10.420 --> 08:12.802
♪ My favorite go-to place
is here with you ♪

08:12.837 --> 08:16.426
♪ My favorite go-to place
is here with you ♪

08:16.461 --> 08:18.843
♪ I've seen the seven wonders

08:18.877 --> 08:20.810
♪ I've felt their mystery

08:20.845 --> 08:22.640
♪ I've climbed
the highest mountains ♪

08:22.674 --> 08:24.434
♪ Sailed across
the deep blue sea ♪

08:24.469 --> 08:27.023
♪ But though I go to
every place I can ♪

08:27.058 --> 08:28.991
♪ Since all my travels
first began ♪

08:29.025 --> 08:30.751
♪ I still look forward to

08:30.786 --> 08:32.891
♪ Each day I spend with you

08:32.926 --> 08:34.617
♪ This much I know is true

08:34.652 --> 08:37.137
♪ My favorite go-to place
is here with you ♪

08:37.171 --> 08:40.830
♪ My favorite go-to place
is here with you ♪

08:40.865 --> 08:42.556
♪ This much I know true

08:42.591 --> 08:44.040
♪ My favorite go-to --

08:44.075 --> 08:45.214
Bernie Klein?

08:45.248 --> 08:46.871
[ All gasp ]You old dog!

08:46.905 --> 08:48.458
That car you sold me
was a lemon!

08:48.493 --> 08:50.322
I want my money back!

08:50.357 --> 08:52.635
Oh, you think you can
just ignore this?

08:52.670 --> 08:54.050
You know what?
You're right.

08:54.085 --> 08:56.259
I'll let my fists
do the rest of the talking.

08:56.294 --> 08:58.538
Hmm?

08:58.572 --> 09:00.850
Hmm?

09:00.885 --> 09:03.750
♪ Though I go to
every place I can ♪

09:03.784 --> 09:05.683
♪ Since all my travels
first began ♪

09:05.717 --> 09:07.581
♪ I still look forward to

09:07.616 --> 09:09.618
♪ Each day I spend with you

09:09.652 --> 09:11.136
♪ This much I know true

09:11.171 --> 09:14.346
♪ My favorite go-to place
is here with you ♪

09:14.381 --> 09:15.865
Mom: "I've never felt more alive

09:15.900 --> 09:18.799
than during our time
at the Watterson's house."

09:18.834 --> 09:21.319
That should do it.

09:21.353 --> 09:22.596
[ All grunting ]

09:22.631 --> 09:25.461
Well, I guess we all
learned a lesson today.

09:25.495 --> 09:27.049
It's okay to commit a crime

09:27.083 --> 09:29.465
if it means you get away with
a different crime.

09:29.499 --> 09:31.605
Nicole,
that's a terrible lesson.

09:31.640 --> 09:33.814
Not every lesson you learn
is a good one.

09:33.849 --> 09:35.505
Bernie:
Uh, what is going on here?

09:35.540 --> 09:38.198
Oh, we're just about to put you
on the last train to glory.

09:38.232 --> 09:42.305
That sounds like some kind
of ghoulish euphemism.

09:42.340 --> 09:44.929
Although we are indeed
from Glory, Minnesota.

09:44.963 --> 09:46.620
But can someone please explain
why you're dragging us

09:46.655 --> 09:49.243
like a couple of slabs of meat
under the cover of darkness?

09:49.278 --> 09:51.452
'Cause you wouldn't wake up
from hibernating!

09:51.487 --> 09:53.593
Hibernating?
Oh, no, like we said,

09:53.627 --> 09:55.042
we do faint
when we get scared.

09:55.077 --> 09:57.389
You didn't get scared.
You had a great time.

09:57.424 --> 09:58.598
Look at your memory map.

09:58.632 --> 09:59.840
Hmm.

09:59.875 --> 10:02.291
This can only mean
one thing.

10:02.325 --> 10:03.948
[ Both gasp ]

10:03.982 --> 10:06.882
This town's most forgettable
place we've ever been to.

10:06.916 --> 10:10.299
But it seems you forgot
something, too.

10:10.333 --> 10:11.369
What?

10:11.403 --> 10:13.336
To ask for your money!

10:13.371 --> 10:16.029
$100, $200, $300.

10:16.063 --> 10:17.340
There you go.

10:17.375 --> 10:19.135
-Thanks.
-Wait a minute!

10:19.170 --> 10:22.207
There's nothing
wrong with that.

10:22.242 --> 10:23.795
I think it's sweet
that you're still in love

10:23.830 --> 10:25.417
after all these years.

10:25.452 --> 10:26.936
You staged these memories.

10:26.971 --> 10:29.042
You rented the house to us
while still hiding in it

10:29.076 --> 10:30.595
and when we saw you
we fainted in shock

10:30.630 --> 10:33.080
and you thought we'd croaked,
so you faked the memory map

10:33.115 --> 10:34.668
and were gonna
put us on the train home

10:34.703 --> 10:35.842
thinking
you'd get away with it.

10:35.876 --> 10:37.050
[ Mom and Dad sigh ]

10:37.084 --> 10:37.844
All: What?!

10:37.878 --> 10:38.914
How did you guess?

10:38.948 --> 10:41.019
We're brother
and sister.

10:42.711 --> 10:45.092
[ Sighs ]
Come on, kids.

10:45.127 --> 10:48.337
That's it.
There's nothing left to eat.

10:48.371 --> 10:52.134
Mm. I guess there is still
one last thing.

10:52.168 --> 10:54.584
♪♪

10:54.619 --> 10:55.689
No.

10:55.724 --> 10:57.173
Yes.

11:02.213 --> 11:09.669
♪♪

11:09.703 --> 11:16.917
♪♪

11:16.952 --> 11:24.166
♪♪

